<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-15T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-15T01:00:00-05:00" n="464" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9377: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-15T14:00:00+08:00">August 15, 1937—2
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 15—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>439. Nanking visited by planes about 2 p.m. which dropped a number of
                                bombs apparently on objectives south of city of Nanking, presumably
                                air field.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>